b'' b'' b'' b'the following are quotations from zionist leaders. they appear in' b'numerous scholarly works dealing with the palestine question. i urge those' b'who have access to original sources, to verify the authenticity of the' b'source and post here their finding, adhering to the truth whatever it be.' b'thanks.' b'elias davidsson' b'------------------------------' b'' b'quotations from zionist leaders' b'' b'1. "there was no such thing as palestinians"' b'(golda meir, prime minister of israel, london sunday' b'times, june b'' b'2. "there is, however, a difficulty from which the zionist' b'dares not avert his eyes, though he rarely likes to face it.' b'palestine proper has already its inhabitants."' b'(israel zangwill, the voice of jerusalem, london b'p.88)' b'' b'3. "when we have settled the land, all the arabs will be' b'able to do about it will be to scurry around like drugged' b'cockroaches in a bottle."' b'(raphael eitan, israeli chief of staff, new york times, b'april b'' b'4. "[the palestinians are] beasts walking on two legs."' b'(menachem begin, prime minister of israel in a speech to' b'the knesset,' b'quoted in amnon kapeliouk, \'begin and the "beasts", new' b'statesman, june b'' b'5. "both the process of expropriation [of the palestinians]' b'and the removal of the poor must be carried out' b'discreetly and circumspectly".' b'(dr. theodor herzl, the complete diaries, herzl press,' b'1960, i., p.88)' b'' b'6. "between ourselves it must be clear that there is no' b'room for both people together in this country...the only' b'solution is a palestine.....without arabs. and there is no' b'other way than to transfer the arabs from here to the' b'neighboring countries, to transfer all of them; not one' b'village, not one tribe, should be left."' b'(joseph weitz, jewish national fund, administrator' b'responsible for zionist colonization. davar, september' b'1967).' b'' b'7."we shall try to spirit the penniless population [the' b'palestinians] across the border by procuring employment' b'for it in the transit countries, while denying it any' b'employment in our own country"' b'(theodor herzl, the complete diaries, herzl press, b'i, p.88)' b'' b'8. "[zionists]...looked for means...to cause the tens of' b'thousands of sulky arabs who remained in the galilee to' b'flee...i gathered all the jewish muktars, who have contact' b'with arabs in different villages and asked them to' b'whisper in the ears of some arabs that a great jewish' b'reinforcement has arrived in galilee and that it is going' b'to burn all of the villages of the huleh. they should' b'suggest to these arabs, as their friends, to escape while' b'there is still time....the tactic reached its goal....wide' b'areas were cleaned."' b'' b"(yig'al alon, sepher ha palmach, in hebrew, ii. p.268," b'quoted in khalidi, from haven to conquest, ips, b'' b'10. "[jews] must expel arabs and take their place"' b'(david ben gurion, quoted in shabtai teveth, ben' b'gurion and the palestine arabs, oxford university press,' b'1985, p. b'' b'11. "we must do everything to ensure they [the' b'palestinian refugees] never do return"' b'(david ben gurion, in his diary, july quoted in' b'michael bar zohar, ben gurion: the armed prophet,' b'prentice-hall, p.157)' b'' b'12. "the country was mostly an empty desert, with only' b'a few islands of arab settlement"' b"(shimon peres, minister of defense, quoted in david's" b'sling: the arming of israel, weidenfeld and nicholson,' b'1970, p.249)' b'' b'13. "all this story about the danger of extermination [of' b'jews] has been blown up....to justify the annexation of' b'new arab territories"' b'(mordechai bentov, israeli cabinet minister, al' b'hamishmar, april b'' b'14. "neither jewish ethics nor jewish tradition can' b'disqualify terrorism as a means of combat"' b'(yitzhak shamir, hehazit, summer [journal of the' b'lehi, the stern gang], translated from the israeli daily' b'al-hamishmar, december b'' b'14. "the domination of jewish agriculture by arab' b'workers is a cancer in our body"' b"(a. uzan, israeli minister of agriculture, ha'aretz, b'december b'' b'15. "there can be only one national home in palestine,' b'and that a jewish one, and no equality in the partnership' b'between jews and arabs"' b'(montague david eder, president of the zionist' b'federation of great britain, b'in doreen ingrams, comp., palestine papers b'seeds of conflict, george braziller, p. b'' b'16. "i hope that the jewish frontiers of palestine will be' b'as great as jewish energy for getting palestine"' b'(dr. chaim weizmann, first president of the state of' b'israel, excerpts from his historic statements, writings' b'and addresses, jewish agency for palestine, p.48)' b'' b'17. "there is not a single jewish village in this country' b'that has not been built on the site of an arab village"' b"(moshe dayan, ha'aretz, april b'' b'18. "some people talk of expelling to b'arabs in the event of a new war, and instruments have' b'been prepared"' b'(aharon yariv, former chief of israeli military' b'intelligence, inquiry, december b'' b'19. "if i was an arab leader i would never make [peace]' b'with israel. that is natural: we have taken their' b'country."' b'(david ben gurion, in nahum goldmann, the jewish' b'paradox, weidenfeld and nicolson, p.99)' b'' b'20. "we should there [in palestine] form a portion of the' b'rampart of europe against asia, an outpost of civilization' b'as opposed to barbarism."' b'(dr. theodor herzl, the jewish state, london, p.' b'29)' b'' b'21. "i deeply believe in launching preventive war' b'against the arab states without further hesitation. by' b'doing so we will achieve two targets: firstly, the' b'annihilation of arab power; and secondly, the expansion' b'of our territory"' b'(menachem begin, in a speech to the knesset, october' b'1955)' b'' b'22. "during the last years our people have been in a' b'process of building up the country and the nation, of' b'expansion, of getting additional jews and additional' b'settlements in order to expand the borders here. let no' b'jew say that the process has ended. let no jew say that' b'we are near the end of the road."' b"(moshe dayan, ma'ariv, july b'' b'23. "until the british left, no jewish settlement, however' b'remote, was entered or seized by the arabs, while the' b'haganah, under severe and frequent attack, captured' b'many arab positions and liberated tiberias and haifa,' b'jaffa and safad"' b'(david ben gurion, rebirth and destiny of israel,' b'philosophical library, p.530)' b'' b'24. "in the months preceding the arab invasion [of' b'1948], and while the five arab states were conducting' b'preparations, we continued to make sallies into arab' b'territory. the conquest of jaffa stands out as an event of' b'first-rate importance in the struggle for hebrew' b'independence early in may, on the eve of the invasion' b'by the five arab states."' b'(menachem begin, the revolt, nash, p.348)' b'' b'25. "what the french could do in tunisia, i said, the jews' b'would be able to do in palestine with jewish will, jewish' b'money, jewish power and jewish enthusiasm"' b'(dr. chaim weizmann, first president of the state of' b'israel, trial and error, harper, p.244)' b'' b'26. "i do not think nasser wanted war. the two divisions' b'he sent to the sinai on may would not have' b'been sufficient to launch an offensive against israel. he' b'knew it and we knew it."' b'(yitzhak rabin, le monde, february b'' b'27. "to pretend that the egyptian forces massed on our' b'frontiers [in were in position to threaten the' b'existence of israel constitutes an insult not only to the' b'intelligence of anyone capable of analyzing this sort of' b'situation, but above all an insult to the zahal [israeli' b'army]"' b"(general res. matti peled, ha'aretz, march b'' b'28. "when we have broken the strength of the arab' b'legion and bombarded amman, we would wipe out' b'transjordan; after that syria would fall....we would thus' b'end the war, and would have put paid to egypt, assyria' b'and chaldea on behalf of our ancestors"' b'(david ben gurion in his diaries, quoted in michael bar-' b'zohar, the armed prophet, a biography of ben-gurion,' b'prentice-hall, p.139)' b'' b'29. "these jews of the diaspora would like to see us, for' b'their own reasons, heroes with our backs to the wall. but' b'this wish can in no way change the realities."' b'(israeli general ezer weizmann, le monde, june b'' b'30. "let us not today fling accusations at the [palestinian' b'arab] murderers. who are we that we should argue' b'against their hatred for eight years now they sit in' b'their refugee camps in gaza, and before their very eyes,' b'we turn into our homestead the land and the villages in' b'which they and their forefathers have lived. we are a' b'generation of settlers, and without the steel helmet and' b'the cannon we cannot plant a tree and build a home. let' b'us not shrink back when we see the hatred fermenting' b'and filling the lives of hundreds of thousands of arabs,' b'who sit all around us. let us not avert our gaze, so that' b'our hand shall not slip. this is the fate of our generation,' b'the choice of our life to be prepared and armed, strong' b'and tough or otherwise, the sword will slip from our' b'first, and our life will be snuffed out."' b'(moshe dayan, eulogy of roy rutenberg at kibbutz nahal' b'oz, quoted in uri avneri, israel without zionists,' b'collier books, macmillan, new york, p.154)' b'' b'' 